					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This inscription is partly built in the wall. It registers the gift of land as <hi rend="italic">Tiruviḍaiyāṭṭam</hi> for supplying sacred offerings such as <hi rend="italic">Tirumālai</hi> (garlands), <hi rend="italic">Tiruparivaṭṭam</hi> (cloth) and <hi rend="italic">Tiruviḷakkeṇṇai</hi> (castor oil) on the occasion of the service, Parākrama Pāṇḍyaṉ <hi rend="italic">sandi</hi> named after the king in the temple of Āḻiṅgapperumāḷ Nayiṉār at Vallanāḍu [Jayaṅ]goṇḍa Pāṇḍyanallūr.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
